President Joseph R. Biden Jr. spoke with President Ivan Duque of Colombia to express support following the attack on the Colombian presidential helicopter. Biden pledged to donate 2.5 million vaccines to Colombia to help combat the COVID-19 pandemic. He also voiced support for peaceful protestors and emphasized the need for law enforcement accountability. The two leaders discussed joint security cooperation, combating the drug trade, promoting economic recovery, and addressing climate change. Biden expressed concern about the situation in Venezuela and stressed the importance of international consensus for free and fair elections.